  "prompt": "How much bands needs to get admission in UC berkeley for indian student after 12th?",
  "response": "To gain admission to UC Berkeley as an international student, including those from India, after completing the 12th grade, you need to meet specific academic and standardized testing requirements. Here's a general overview:\n\n1. **Academics**: \n   - Strong academic performance in high school (grades 9-12).\n   - Completion of courses that meet UC's subject requirement pattern (A-G requirements).\n   - Competitive GPA, generally well above 3.5 on a 4.0 scale.\n\n2. **Standardized Tests**:\n   - As of recent changes, UC Berkeley and other UC schools have adopted a \"test-optional\" policy due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This means SAT or ACT scores are not required, but you can submit them if you believe they will strengthen your application.\n\n3. **English Language Proficiency**:\n   - If you come from a non-English speaking country, you will need to demonstrate English proficiency. For UC Berkeley, acceptable tests include:\n     - IELTS: A minimum overall band score of 7.0.\n     - TOEFL: A minimum score of 80 on the internet-based test (iBT).\n\n4. **Other Requirements**:\n   - Personal Insight Questions.\n   - Extracurricular activities and leadership roles.\n   - Letters of recommendation (optional but recommended).\n\n5. **Financial Considerations**:\n   - Ability to fund your education, as international students may not be eligible for federal financial aid.\n\nIt's important to check the official UC Berkeley admissions website for the most up-to-date and specific requirements, as admission criteria can change.",
